org.hl7.fhir.dstu3.validation

Interface IResourceValidator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    InstanceValidator

    public interface IResourceValidator
    Interface to the instance validator. This takes a resource, in one of many forms, and checks whether it is valid
    Author:
    Grahame Grieve

      • validate

        void validate(Object Context,
              List<ValidationMessage> errors,
              Element element)
       throws Exception
        Validate suite you can validate one of the following representations of resources: stream - provide a format - this is the preferred choice Use one of these two if the content is known to be valid XML/JSON, and already parsed - a DOM element or Document - a Json Object In order to use these, the content must already be parsed - e.g. it must syntactically valid - a native resource - a elementmodel resource in addition, you can pass one or more profiles ti validate beyond the base standard - as structure definitions or canonical URLs
        Throws:
        Exception
